  "prompt": "Should I skip school because of suicide thoughts?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry to hear that you're feeling this way. It\u2019s important to take your mental health seriously, and suicidal thoughts are a sign that you need support and care. Here\u2019s what I recommend:\n\n1. **Reach Out for Help Immediately**: Talk to someone you trust, like a family member, friend, teacher, or school counselor. You don\u2019t have to face this alone.\n\n2. **Contact a Crisis Hotline**: There are professionals available 24/7 to help. If you're in the U.S., you can call or text 988 for the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline. If you're in another country, there are similar services available.\n\n3. **Prioritize Your Mental Health**: If you feel overwhelmed and unsafe, it\u2019s okay to take a step back. However, staying connected to supportive people and resources is crucial.\n\n4. **Consider Speaking with Your School**: If you feel comfortable, let your school know what you\u2019re going through. They may be able to provide accommodations or support.\n\n5. **Talk to a Mental Health Professional**: A therapist or counselor can help you work through these feelings and develop coping strategies. If you\u2019re not already seeing someone, consider reaching out.\n\nYour life is valuable, and there are people who care about you and want to help. Please don\u2019t hesitate to seek support\u2014you deserve it.",
